originalText.text:
I found myself in a pinch right before a road trip from NYC to Detroit, and this dealership was a lifesaver. Not only did they expedite my oil change and tire rotation with impeccable efficiency, but they treated me like I was part of the family. While waiting, I indulged in one of the finest lattes I've ever had, thanks to their top-notch coffee machine.

A special shoutout to Nelson and Jonathan. Their genuine care and support didn't go unnoticed. They even took the time to give me a tour around the dealership, adding a cherry on top of an already delightful experience.

Gratitude doesn't even begin to cover it. If youâ€™re in Manhattan, I know exactly where youâ€™ll want to be  heading. One of the best dealership experiences hands down. Highly recommended!

originalText.text:
Woke up on Wednesday the 31 of January only to discover that my Dodge Ram would not start( the engine would not turn over). I had to get my truck towed for assessment/repair. Called Chrysler Dodge prior to the truck being towed to see if they could see me. The gentleman, I believe Matt said, "Bring the truck in, but I have to be honest." We won't be able to assess any issues until Friday. I'm like, cool! Arrived at the dealership. I believe Manny was the service tech who greeted me. He will definitely disarm you with a positive spirit. He slides in some warm heartened humor along the way. Even tried to get me to think about purchasing a new truck if I suddenly fell out of love with my existing truck. Checked in with the service desk. The entire team said Good Morning. You only get that type of group acknowledgment if you're at Chick-fil-A.  Matt shared that he would call me on Friday with an update. Cool! Fast forward to Thursday around 1:00 p.m. Matt called me and stated that I'm all good. You can pick up the truck. Not only did I not get my truck four days earlier than I anticipated( I definitely had the mindset that I won't get the truck until Monday or Tuesday factoring in the weekend) But as I am driving away, truck washed and interior cleaned. It just so happens that it is raining. I hate when that occurs. I remembered that I had to get an oil changed. But, the notification was not displayed on the console. I'm like what's up? They gave me an oil change!!!!! Saved me $150.00
Blessed  ðŸ™Œ

originalText.text: Immersed on Manhattan's West Side is the treasure of a team at Jeep of Manhattan. This review is for their stellar Service Department which falls nothing short of stellar. Enter into a very clean space filled with the kindest leadership and caring receptionists who will carefully listen to all of your concerns and manage all of your vehicle's needs. I had an issue that was immediately corrected and helped profusely by a very well-trained staff who genuinely insisted on helping my family. My car has always been treated respectfully and I am very happy with the work at every visit. Feel free to enjoy a nice treat from their fully stocked coffee bar and know you will always be kept aware of the repairs needed on your vehicle. John in the Service department is one of the most detail-oriented and caring leaders Jeep has ever employed. He should train the rest of Chrysler Dodge Jeep Ram Fiats throughout the nation. In addition, every vehicle serviced receives their 5-star car wash managed by Nelson and his team of hard working professionals who leave your vehicle cleaned in perfect condition and who always go the extra mile for their customers. The best receptionists always treat everyone with a smile and are fully equipped to answer hard questions and put the client at ease. This service team has been the best since owning my Jeep and I can share that my experiences at Manhattan Chrysler Service has been incredible. I appreciate everyone there and can't wait to see the team again.

originalText.text: Lou Gashi is the best.  I came in just to look at jeep options and walked away with a 2024 Jeep Sahara.  He has excellent customer service and gave his honest opinion on the vehicles.  If you are looking for a new vehicle please ask for Lou!
